---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { STATS } from '../../data/stats';
---

<BaseLayout
  pageType="guide"
  guideTopic="condition"
  title="Shipping Container Condition Guide — Wind & Water Tight | Steel Box Direct"
  description="What container condition means. Every container we sell is Wind & Water Tight (used) — structurally sound, weather-tight, and storage-ready at the best value."
  datePublished="2026-03-10"
  dateModified="2026-05-26"
>
  <div class="guide-header guide_header" style="background: var(--c2-cond); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sh guide_eyebrow" style="border-color: var(--cream);">
        <span class="idx">§ 02</span>
        <span class="nm" style="color: var(--cream);">Decision: Condition</span>
        <span class="tg" style="color: var(--cream);">ISO 9096 Standards</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="big guide_headline" style="color: var(--cream);">Used Steel.<br><em>Built to Last.</em></h1>
      <p class="guide-lede guide_lede" style="opacity: .9;">
        Every container we sell is Wind & Water Tight — used steel that's structurally sound and seals out
        rain, wind, and snow, at {STATS.usedSavingsVsNew.value} less than new. Here's exactly what that means in practice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="guide-content guide_content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="row guide_main_row">
        <div class="main-col guide_main_col">
          <h2>What "Wind & Water Tight" Means</h2>
          <p>Shipping containers are graded by their remaining useful life. Every container we sell is <strong>Wind & Water Tight (used)</strong> — the grade that does everything most buyers need at the best value.</p>
          <p style="font-weight: 600;">Structurally sound, sealed against the weather, and storage-ready — at a fraction of the cost of new.</p>

          <div class="grade-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--c2-cond);">
            <h3>Wind & Water Tight (WWT)</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--c2-cond); margin-bottom: 12px;">Our Standard Grade · 10+ Years of Service</div>
            <p>A used container, retired from years of cargo service, that still keeps rain, wind, snow, and pests out and stays structurally sound on the ground. Expect visible wear from that working life — surface rust, scratches, dents, and marked or previously patched areas, with floors that may show staining or wear — over weathering (Cor-Ten) steel built to last decades. It's honest, working-grade steel: not cosmetically perfect, but sealed and sound for storage.</p>
            <div class="who guide_comparison_item_tag" style="background: var(--yellow); color: var(--ink);">→ Best Value</div>
          </div>

          <div class="grade-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--ink);">
            <h3>What to Know</h3>
            <p>Our containers are sold as-is for storage and on-site use — weather-tight and built to last, but not certified for ocean shipping. For storage, workshop, and conversion projects, that certification simply isn't needed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar-col guide_sidebar_col">
          <div class="authority-card guide_callout">
            <div class="m guide_callout_label">The Reality Check</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Wind &amp; Water Tight</strong> — sealed against rain, wind, snow, and pests.</li>
              <li><strong>{STATS.usedSavingsVsNew.value} less</strong> than buying new.</li>
              <li><strong>Decades</strong> of service life from weathering (Cor-Ten) steel.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-card guide_cta">
            <h4 class="guide_cta_headline">Ready to quote?</h4>
            <p>We'll give you a real number for your container.</p>
            <a href="/quote/" class="btn guide_cta_btn">Get My Quote <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .guide-header {
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
      border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .guide-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
      max-width: 720px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .guide-content {
      padding: 96px 0;
      background: var(--cream);
    }

    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 80px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .grade-card {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    }
    .grade-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 28px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .who {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: .08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .authority-card {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      padding: 32px;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .authority-card .m { color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .authority-card li { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.45; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(246,241,231,.1); padding-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .cta-card {
      margin-top: 40px;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--c1-size);
    }
    .cta-card h4 { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .cta-card p { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .guide-header { padding: 48px 0; }
      .big { font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 80px); }
    }
    .guide-next { padding: 48px 0; background: var(--ink); border-top: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08); }
    .guide-next-label { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .1em; color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .guide-next-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; }
    .guide-next-links a { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--cream); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); padding-bottom: 2px; }
    .guide-next-links a:hover { color: var(--yellow); border-color: var(--yellow); }
  </style>

  <section class="guide-next">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="guide-next-label">Continue researching</p>
      <div class="guide-next-links">
        <a href="/cost/">What does a container cost?</a>
        <a href="/permits/">Do I need a permit?</a>
        <a href="/delivery/">How is it delivered?</a>
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/">Browse container specs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="guide-product-cta" style="padding: 64px 0; background: var(--ink); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 24px; max-width: 680px;">
      <p class="m" style="color: var(--yellow); margin: 0;">Ready to buy?</p>
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0; line-height: 1.05;">Browse containers by size</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 17px; opacity: .75; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;">Wind &amp; Water Tight (used) steel — see what's available in your area.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/" class="btn" style="background: var(--yellow); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--yellow);">View All Containers →</a>
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/40-foot-high-cube-container/" class="btn-ghost" style="color: var(--cream);">40ft High Cube</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
